In September 17, Le Devour published a letter from Mr. Patrick J. Garver, vice-president of the Canadian mining company Barrick Gold.
Pursuing an Orwellian logic, the latter claims that the world's largest gold company has filed a defamation complaint of six million against three authors and a small publisher house broken down with the intention of launching a "transparent public debate".
If it is true that judges are independent and impartial, it is not the truth that they judge, especially in the case of a defamation dispute, but the law.
