Open Office, here's the third edition of the "anti-Microsoft" package
It is the day of OpenOffice.org's release 3.0, the open-source suite of personal productivity that aims to reach more and more users, from home to office, from professionals to public administration, as a free alternative to the best known Microsoft Office.
After nearly a year's work by voluntary developers, whose backs are monitored by SUN Microsystem, the new Open Office is shown to the general public with different news: to the welcome screen and to the revised and made less spartan interface, they add more substantial ones such as native compatibility for the Apple Mac OS X operating system and support for the new ODF format (Open Document Format) 1.2, the latest standard ISO version.
Attention also put to interoperability with the Office 2007 suite, Open Office is able to open documents with the new Microsoft extension (.docx, .xlsx, .pptx).
Interesting are some specific features of some modules such as that which allows you to reduce the size of PowerPoint presentations, useful for example to send them via e-mail, or the possibility to import PDF files into the graphics processing module, preserving the original look of the page.
Also on this front you can create documents "hybrid PDF", which combine the typical graphics of Adobe format with elements of a spreadsheet or a text computer.
Collaboration is an element that has received several improvements within applications: in the spreadsheet you can intervene by hands between different users, avoiding conflicts on changes, in the text maker, each employee is assigned a color in comments for better recognition in the review phase.
Some companies are also working to bring some features of OpenOffice on the Web (on the cloud, on the cloud), and in the coming weeks they should release the final result.
The version in Italian is available at http://it.openoffice.org/download/3.0.0/download300.html and is added to the English version that was on the mirrors from Friday.
In addition to Windows and Mac OS, as usual the suite is also available for the Linux operating system.
On request you can also send the installation cd to your home or workplace.
And if the theme of gratuity can be a drive to spread in houses, it is precisely in business that Open Office the suite tries the big bet, and can already count on several projects made in public administration and schools.
And there are also realities that offer an ideal training, advice and assistance service for small and medium-sized companies, which could open up business prospects.
Open Office consists of five main modules: Writer, for the corresponding videowriting of Word; Calc, is the spreadsheet that aims to replace Excel; Impress, for the emulate presentations of Powerpoint; Dbase, as in the case of the most famous Access is the program that allows you to work on the databases; Draw, is finally the graphic module.
The objective for 2008 is to reach 5 million downloads, and considering that today we are nearly 3 million and 600 thousand, with the release of the new version it is likely that you can also exceed the expected figure.
